metadata.description:
e 9 A i - the voices in my head

“it’s all about the stories we repeatedly tell ourselves ... those insidious voices in our heads whispering over and over and over … wearing grooves in our brain … pathways of repetition that become the ruts we get stuck in … come to think of it … kind of like a programming language … a looping script that we mindlessly follow … 

in the beginning was the word and the word was a programming language … but then the scripts became stories … and the stories began to write their own stories … and this is how free-will was born …

so … change your story, change your life … go forth and (re)write your own damn script.”
